  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Multi-Sectoral Assistance to Cyclone Idai Affected Population in Zimbabwe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM aims at improving human security by providing multi-sector assistance to individuals and communities affected by cyclone Idai and recurrent droughts in Manicaland Province by strengthening their resilience for future crisis. In order to address the acute needs of displaced and vulnerable communities who have been affected, IOM is undertaking humanitarian interventions with a multi-sector approach in the areas of Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), camp coordination and camp management, disaster risk reduction and shelter.</narrative>
  </description>
